        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="2"/><name>Cornelius</name>
                    <lb n="3"/><name>Epa<foreign xml:lang="la-Grek">φ</foreign>ruitus</name>
                    <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>vix</abbr><ex>it</ex></expan> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>an</abbr><ex>nos</ex></expan> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <num value="8">VIII</num>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>CIL</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To the shades of the underworld. Cornelius Epaphruitus lived for 8 years.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Korhonen convincingly makes the case that this is a Sicilian inscription, from Termini, not an Urban inscription from Rome. He additionally notes the rarity of linguistic interference as here, in the Termini Latin inscriptions.</p>
            </div>
